title: FC Trudovye Rezervy-RIPO Minsk
content:
FC Trudovye Rezervy-RIPO Minsk or FK Pracownyya Rezyervy-RIPA (Belarusian: ФК Працоўныя рэзервы-РІПА) was a football club based in Minsk, Belarus.

The club was founded as a partnership between Minsk branch of Trudovye Rezervy Sport Society (Pracownyya Rezyervy) and Republican Institute for Vocational Education (Respublikanskiy Institut Professionalnogo Obrazovaniya or Respublikanski Instytut Prafesiynay Adukatsyi in Belarusian).[a] In 2001 they joined Belarusian Second League, where they only played for one season. In 2002 the club merged with FC Traktor Minsk to form MTZ-RIPO Minsk.
